      "asbval:note": "No mention of methylRawListDB, tabix-backed storage, or such a pipeline in the paper. The paper does mention memory efficiency in the context of reading multiple experiments simultaneously (passage 4: 'methylKit can read and store (in memory) methylation data simultaneously for N-experiments, limited only by memory of the node or computer'), but not in relation to tabix-indexed bgzipped files or database paths.",
