    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The candidate card describes advanced features (tabix-indexed bgzipped file storage, methylRawListDB objects, database paths, metadata headers) that are not present in the 2012 methylKit paper (v0.5.3). These features may have been added in later versions of methylKit (\u22651.13.1), but the paper passages provided do not cover such functionality.",
        "The paper focuses on basic input/output (text files and SAM files), in-memory analysis, and visualization. The card's focus on disk-based tabix-backed storage represents a significant scope drift from the paper's actual content.",
        "The version mentioned in the card (\u22651.13.1) is substantially newer than the version described in the paper (v0.5.3, published 2012), suggesting the card may be extracting from documentation or examples for a much later version of the software."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
