    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/dna-methylation-differential-analysis/010",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "In logistic regression, information from each sample is specified (the number of methylated Cs and number of unmethylated Cs at a given region), and a logistic regression test will be applied to compare fraction of methylated Cs across the test and the control groups... Additional covariates can be incorporated into model (1) by adding to the right side of the model: \u03b1 1 \u2217 Covariate 1,i + ... + \u03b1 K \u2217 Covariate K,i",
      "asbval:note": "Fully supported. Paper provides detailed description of logistic regression method with treatment indicators and covariate support.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2012-13-10-r87",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "dna-methylation-differential-analysis",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "methods",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Logistic regression method for differential methylation analysis with treatment indicator variable and optional covariates",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:16:49.517155+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/dna-methylation-differential-analysis/011",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The Fisher's exact test compares the fraction of methylated Cs in test and control samples in the absence of replicates... In practice, the number of samples per group will determine which of the two methods will be used (logistic regression or Fisher's exact test). If there are multiple samples per group, methyl Kit will employ the logistic regression test. Otherwise, when there is one sample per group, Fisher's exact test will be used.",
      "asbval:note": "Fully supported. Paper describes Fisher's exact test as alternative method for single-sample-per-group scenarios.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2012-13-10-r87",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "dna-methylation-differential-analysis",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "methods",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Fisher's exact test method for differential methylation analysis when sample replication is limited",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:16:49.517155+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/dna-methylation-differential-analysis/012",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "the base/region would subsequently be classified as a differentially methylated cytosine (DMC) or region (DMR)... We have designed methyl Kit to allow a user to specify the parameters that define the DMCs/DMRs based on: q-value, %methylation difference, and type of differential methylation (hypo-/hyper-).",
      "asbval:note": "Confirmed. Paper explicitly describes DMC and DMR outputs with q-value and methylation difference filtering.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-gb-2012-13-10-r87",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "dna-methylation-differential-analysis",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Differentially methylated cytosines (DMCs) and differentially methylated regions (DMRs) with q-values and methylation difference percentages",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
