    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/methylation-data-clustering/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "PCA can reduce the high dimensionality of a data set by transforming the large number of regions to a few principal components... are often used to emphasize grouping structure in the data... a plot of the first two or three principal components could potentially reveal a biologically meaningful clustering of the samples",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly describes how PCA reveals grouping structure and sample subpopulations.",
